A KwaZulu-Natal cop was speared to death while rushing to help a woman who was stabbed.The Newcastle K9 Unit Warrant Officer Sascha Naidoo, was responding to the incident with other officers at Section 7P in Madadeni today.Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said it was not immediately clear if the woman was also attacked with a spear."While approaching the suspect, it is alleged that the suspect stabbed Naidoo with a spear and he sustained serious injuries."Gwala said the 45-year-old officer was rushed to a local hospital for treatment where he later died."The 59-year-old suspect was overpowered... and immediately placed under arrest."KwaZulu-Natal acting police commissioner, Major-General Bheki Langa said he was shocked at the incident, but commended Naidoo for his bravery."The member died in the line of duty when he was needed the most. He was performing his duty to protect and serve the community of Madadeni when he was attacked."Langa condemned the killing saying the local community must "stand up and get involved in stopping this kind of attack.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/kzn-cop-speared-to-death-20170630